# Project - Prep #1

## Cooperation Plan

1. What are the key strengths of each person on the team?
Anthony - Super cool, great music taste, self-proclaimed chef, crazy 808 patterns. Mildly impulsive, let’s intrusive thoughts win more often than not. (Anthony-proclaimed)
Resilience, flexibility, adaptability, Leadership/Mentorship. 
Alejandra - Great food taste, crazy spice tolerance, crazy spicy, great hair, cute bags. Excellent coding adaptability. (Anthony-proclaimed)
Leadership, organizational skills, attention to detail, and problem solving.
David - Strong gamer, excellent hand-eye coordination, improvisational adaptability, resilience, tinkerer and mecha-gnome. Is mad decent in Smash bros. Do not recommend it. (Anthony-proclaimed)
I think I do a decent job of lightening the mood in a stressful situation. Try and find the good in things. 

2. How can you best utilize these strengths in the execution of your project?
Combining our set of skills can help face the dynamics of this project. We will all be able to work together to compromise and come to a solution or create features that will amp up our project. 

3. In which professional competencies do you each want to develop greater strength?
Anthony - Incremental Delivery - I have a bad habit of working all through an assignment/project at once and then delivering a product. I need to work on delivering parts as I go so that I can adjust direction if needed.
Alejandra - Public speaking, openness and confidence
David - Technical, Confidence, and collaboration. 

4. Knowing that every person in your team needs to understand all aspects of the project, how do you plan to approach the day-to-day work?
Anthony - Trying to maintain a schedule that is centralized around preparation so that we understand what the next day’s work looks like.
Alejandra - Working on communicating my ideas and contributing. 
David - Communicating my intentions for the work I wanna do, then find out the work that my classmates are going to do so we’re all on the same page. 


## Conflict Plan 

1. What will be your group’s process to resolve conflict, when it arises?
The process would be to hear all perspectives and discuss how to resolve it. 
What will your team do if one person is taking over the project and not letting the other members contribute? 
We will express our concerns of being excluded from the project, and we will be open and try to find a solution we can all agree on.

2. How will you approach each other and the challenges of the project knowing that it is impossible for all members to be at the exact same place in understanding and skill level?
We are a team, and we will all strive to do our best at our own pace! Its okay to do things at different paces, in the end we will make it work out!!! :D Heck yeah team !!B@ang B@ang!!

3. How will you raise concerns to members who are not adequately contributing?
Anthony - I will bring it to their attention one on one first, then bring in the rest of the group if nothing changes, and continue to elevate responsibility as needed until the issue is resolved.

4. How and when will you escalate the conflict if your resolution attempts are unsuccessful?
 Anthony - see above ^


## Communication Plan 

1. What hours will you be available to communicate?
9am-6pm

2. What platforms will you use to communicate (ie. Slack, phone …)?
Slack and discord

3.How often will you take breaks?
Whenever we see fit, sometimes the work keeps flowing and others we need to just step away to recollect our thoughts.

4.What is your plan if you start to fall behind?
Lock down and set what we need to accomplish on what day before we end our collaboration day.

5. How will you communicate after hours and on the weekend? 
We can reach out through phones or slack since most have the mobile app as well.

6. What is your strategy for ensuring everyone’s voice is heard?
When discussing a topic we will have everyone lay out their opinions and ideas and just come to a vote on which path to take.

7.How will you ensure that you are creating a safe environment where everyone feels comfortable speaking up?
Having a good connection with your peers and everyone has an openness to different ways of thinking.

## Work Plan

1. How will you identify tasks, assign tasks, know when they are complete, and manage work in general?
We will work together to create a list of tasks, and identify any other tasks we will need to do, then we will work together to figure out the best way to complete all of them.

2. What project management tool will be used?
GitHub, and Discord. We will keep in touch and communicate as much as possible.


## Git Process

1. What components of your project will live on GitHub?
Majority if not all of the project. 

2. How will you share the repository with your teammates?
Created an organization so everyone has ownership of the repository.

3. What is your Git flow?
Main > Staging > Local. Everything will be located collectively on each team member's laptop, and when ready will be sent to a staging branch for review before being merged into main.

4. Will you be using a PR review workflow? If so, consider:
- How many people must review a PR?
We are going to have 3 people review 
- Who merges PRs?
Alejandra will merge PRs 
- How often will you merge?
Once we’ve successfully implemented any features then we will ACP and merge.
- How will you communicate that it’s time to merge?
We will discuss what we’ve gotten done and make sure there are no conflicts, and once we collectively agree will merge. 
